The paper deals with the construction of expanders using lifts, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and spectral graph theory (cs.SD). The use of representation theory principles suggests that the paper may also fall under information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of the eigenvalues of the adjacency matrix involves numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the study of group actions and Cayley graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry and topology (cs.GT).
